Hello I’m Shabeena, beauty coach, a registered nurse 👩‍⚕️ , and now a proud founder of a growing skincare brand rooted in healing, simplicity, and results ✅

My skincare journey started not in a lab, but in the hospital wards — where I understood skin not just as beauty, but as biology. 

That passion led me to pursue an internationally certified CIDESCO diploma in Skincare & Facial Aesthetics 

Now I’m soon completing my certification as a **skincare formulator** too 🥹 — so you can bet every drop and bar from Shifara is backed by science and care 🤌🏻

I created @shifarabeauty with a mission to blend tradition with modern skin science — and we’re just getting started. From our bestselling *Rosemary Hydrosol* to our nourishing *Goat milk bar soap* (Launching soon 🙈) every product is handmade with purpose and deep understanding of Indian skin needs.

But Shabeena isn’t just a brand — it’s a *coaching space* too! 
I offer - custom skincare coaching for anyone feeling lost, stuck, or just tired of jumping from product to product with no results.
We don’t do “one-size-fits-all” here — we do *your* skin, *your* way.

To all my new followers — welcome to a space that’s all about healing, glow-ups, and good vibes 😚 (plus a little chai on the side)

Now tell me — what’s one thing you wish someone told you earlier about skincare 🫶🏻

Let’s chat in the comments!

So I finally tried the @medicube_global_official PDRN Overnight Sheet Mask—yes, the one you actually sleep in 🤭

At first, I’ll be honest—I wasn’t sure how I’d survive the night with a sheet stuck to my face. 
It felt a little uncomfortable initially, but surprisingly, it settled in so well after a few minutes and didn’t move at all while I slept!

🎀 What I loved most?
It comes with under-eye patches and two extra patches for smile lines—which honestly made me feel like I was in a mini facial session at home.

When I woke up, my skin felt hydrated, fresh, and visibly plump. The one you see like glass skin yes 🙌 it gave the glass skin finish for a day 😍 which honestly surprised me. That post-mask glow was definitely worth it.

But since it’s on the expensive side, I’d suggest keeping this for special events—like weddings, shoots, or any day your skin needs to bring its A-game.

As a beauty coach, I always say—not every day needs luxury skincare, but some days definitely do.
